   "source": [
    "# Network Traffic Classification Using Transformer-Enhanced LSTM Models\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook runs the proposed Transformer-Enhanced LSTM model only. Published baseline results are used for discussion in the research paper, but no baseline model is trained inside this project."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "Import the reusable project pipeline from the `src/` directory."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "\n",
    "PROJECT_ROOT = Path.cwd().parent if Path.cwd().name == 'notebooks' else Path.cwd()\n",
    "SRC_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / 'src'\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, str(SRC_DIR))\n",
    "\n",
    "from preprocessing import prepare_dataset\n",
    "from train import run_project\n",
    "\n",
    "PROJECT_ROOT"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7e2cb679",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Experiment Settings\n",
    "\n",
    "Choose `cic`, `unsw`, or `all`. Leave `EPOCHS` and `BATCH_SIZE` as `None` to use the strong dataset-specific defaults from `src/config.py`. Training now runs the full configured epoch schedule and restores the best validation-accuracy weights at the end."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "965ac542",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "RUN_MODE = 'cic'  # options: 'cic', 'unsw', 'all'\n",
    "EPOCHS = None  # None uses tuned default: CIC=180, UNSW=140\n",
    "BATCH_SIZE = None  # None uses tuned default: CIC=192, UNSW=128\n",
    "MAX_SAMPLES = None  # keep None for final Colab training; use a small number only for quick testing\n",
    "CLASS_WEIGHT_MODE = 'auto'  # auto uses the tuned setting from src/config.py\n",
    "SAVE_MODEL = True\n",
    "SEED = 42"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "02257ef2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Preview Preprocessing\n",
    "\n",
    "This preview confirms feature shape, class labels, and split distributions. It uses a small sample and does not affect final training."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "17360418",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "preview_datasets = ['cic', 'unsw'] if RUN_MODE == 'all' else [RUN_MODE]\n",
    "\n",
    "for dataset_key in preview_datasets:\n",
    "    data = prepare_dataset(dataset=dataset_key, data_dir=PROJECT_ROOT / 'dataset', max_samples=1000)\n",
    "    print(f'\\nDataset: {data.dataset_name}')\n",
    "    print('Label column:', data.label_column)\n",
    "    print('Input shape:', data.input_shape)\n",
    "    print('Classes:', data.class_names)\n",
    "    print('Train tensor:', data.X_train.shape)\n",
    "    print('Validation tensor:', data.X_val.shape)\n",
    "    print('Test tensor:', data.X_test.shape)\n",
    "    print('Class distribution:', data.class_distribution)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8198acc5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Train and Evaluate Proposed Model\n",
    "\n",
    "This cell trains only the Transformer-Enhanced LSTM, runs the full configured epoch schedule, restores the best validation-accuracy weights, and writes proposed-model metrics and figures."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if RUN_MODE not in {'cic', 'unsw', 'all'}:\n",
    "    raise ValueError(\"RUN_MODE must be one of: 'cic', 'unsw', 'all'\")\n",
    "\n",
    "experiments = run_project(\n",
    "    dataset='cic' if RUN_MODE == 'all' else RUN_MODE,\n",
    "    all_datasets=(RUN_MODE == 'all'),\n",
    "    data_dir=PROJECT_ROOT / 'dataset',\n",
    "    results_dir=PROJECT_ROOT / 'results',\n",
    "    figures_dir=PROJECT_ROOT / 'figures',\n",
    "    epochs=EPOCHS,\n",
    "    batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,\n",
    "    max_samples=MAX_SAMPLES,\n",
    "    class_weight_mode=CLASS_WEIGHT_MODE,\n",
    "    save_model=SAVE_MODEL,\n",
    "    seed=SEED,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "list(experiments.keys())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Display Metrics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "metrics_file = {\n",
    "    'cic': PROJECT_ROOT / 'results' / 'cic_darknet2020_metrics.txt',\n",
    "    'unsw': PROJECT_ROOT / 'results' / 'unsw_nb15_metrics.txt',\n",
    "    'all': PROJECT_ROOT / 'results' / 'metrics.txt',\n",
    "}[RUN_MODE]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(metrics_file)\n",
    "print(metrics_file.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Display Figures"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from IPython.display import Image, display\n",
    "\n",
    "prefix = {'cic': 'cic_darknet2020_', 'unsw': 'unsw_nb15_', 'all': ''}[RUN_MODE]\n",
    "figure_paths = [\n",
    "    PROJECT_ROOT / 'results' / f'{prefix}confusion_matrix.png',\n",
    "    PROJECT_ROOT / 'figures' / f'{prefix}accuracy_curve.png',\n",
    "    PROJECT_ROOT / 'figures' / f'{prefix}loss_curve.png',\n",
    "]\n",
    "if RUN_MODE == 'all':\n",
    "    figure_paths.append(PROJECT_ROOT / 'figures' / 'dataset_comparison_graph.png')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "for path in figure_paths:\n",
    "    print(path)\n",
    "    if path.exists():\n",
    "        display(Image(filename=str(path)))\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print('Missing file. Run the training cell first.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Summary Table"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "rows = []\n",
    "for dataset_key, experiment in experiments.items():\n",
    "    result = experiment['metrics']\n",
    "    rows.append({\n",
    "        'Dataset': experiment['dataset_name'],\n",
    "        'Model': result['model_name'],\n",
    "        'Accuracy': result['accuracy'],\n",
    "        'Weighted F1': result['weighted_f1'],\n",
    "        'Macro F1': result['macro_f1'],\n",
    "        'Weighted AUC': result['weighted_auc'],\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    import pandas as pd\n",
    "    display(pd.DataFrame(rows))\n",
    "except Exception:\n",
    "    rows"
   ]
  }
